    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A water-soluble polymer, commonly known as carboxymethylcellulose (CMC), composed of the sodium salt of modified cellulose. A viscous gel when dispersed in water at low concentrations, CMC forms a tough, non-soluble film in reaction with heavy metal salts. In conservation, it is used as an adhesive and as a poultice for cleaning stone.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
